+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01B4f7L6hAh2xeLRWkQ6Eb6K","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0195ZDTrAUPcGAvpxQDofQnx","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-time-tracker.md","content":"# CLI Time Tracker Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a TypeScript time tracking library that supports starting/stopping timers, JSON persistence, querying by date range, and per-task summaries.\n\n**Architecture:** Single `TimeTracker` class backed by a JSON file. Entries stored as an array of `{task, start, end?}` objects. The class manages a \"current\" running timer and auto-stops it when a new one starts. All file I/O uses Node.js `fs` built-ins with `mkdirSync` for auto-creating directories.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict, ES2022, Node16 modules), Node.js built-in `fs` and `path` modules, Vitest for tests.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Install dependencies and scaffold types\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts` (initial stub)\n\n**Step 1: Install npm dependencies**\n\nRun: `npm install`\nExpected: Clean install\n\n**Step 2: Create the `TimeEntry` interface**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nexport interface TimeEntry {\n  task: string;\n  start: string;   // ISO 8601\n  end: string | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create stub `src/index.ts`**\n\n```typescript\n// src/index.ts\nexport { TimeTracker } from \"./tracker.js\";\nexport type { TimeEntry } from \"./types.js\";\n```\n\n**Step 4: Verify build fails (tracker doesn't exist yet)**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: FAIL (tracker.js not found)\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement the TimeTracker class — constructor and persistence\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/tracker.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the `TimeTracker` class with constructor and persistence helpers**\n\n```typescript\n// src/tracker.ts\nimport { mkdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync, existsSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { dirname } from \"node:path\";\nimport type { TimeEntry } from \"./types.js\";\n\nexport class TimeTracker {\n  private filePath: string;\n  private entries: TimeEntry[];\n\n  constructor(filePath: string) {\n    this.filePath = filePath;\n    this.entries = this.load();\n  }\n\n  private load(): TimeEntry[] {\n    if (!existsSync(this.filePath)) {\n      return [];\n    }\n    const raw = readFileSync(this.filePath, \"utf-8\");\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as TimeEntry[];\n  }\n\n  private save(): void {\n    const dir = dirname(this.filePath);\n    mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });\n    writeFileSync(this.filePath, JSON.stringify(this.entries, null, 2), \"utf-8\");\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify build passes**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement start/stop timer logic\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/tracker.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add `start()` method**\n\nThe `start(task)` method should:\n- Throw if `task` is empty or whitespace-only\n- Auto-stop any currently running timer\n- Push a new entry with `end: null`\n- Save to disk\n\n**Step 2: Add `stop()` method**\n\nThe `stop()` method should:\n- Throw if no timer is running\n- Set `end` on the running entry to current ISO time\n- Save to disk\n\n**Step 3: Add helper to find running entry**\n\n```typescript\nprivate findRunning(): TimeEntry | undefined {\n  return this.entries.find((e) => e.end === null);\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Verify build passes**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit`\nExpected: PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Implement query and summary methods\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/tracker.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add `getEntries(start?, end?)` method**\n\nReturns all entries, optionally filtered by date range (inclusive). Compare entry `start` time against the range.\n\n**Step 2: Add `getSummary()` method**\n\nReturns a `Record<string, number>` mapping task names to total milliseconds. Running entries use `Date.now()` for their end time.\n\n**Step 3: Verify build and lint pass**\n\nRun: `npx tsc --noEmit && npx eslint src/`\nExpected: PASS\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Write comprehensive tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/__tests__/tracker.test.ts`\n\n**Tests to write:**\n1. Start a timer and verify entry is created with `end: null`\n2. Stop a timer and verify `end` is set\n3. Starting a new timer auto-stops the previous one\n4. `stop()` throws when nothing is running\n5. `start(\"\")` throws for empty name\n6. Persistence: create tracker, start/stop, create new tracker with same file, verify data loaded\n7. Auto-creates directories for file path\n8. `getEntries()` returns all entries\n9. `getEntries()` filters by date range\n10. `getSummary()` sums durations per task\n11. Unicode/emoji task names work correctly\n\n**Step 1: Write tests**\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\nRun: `npm test`\nExpected: All pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Final validation\n\n**Step 1:** Run `npm run build`\n**Step 2:** Run `npm run lint`\n**Step 3:** Run `npm test`\n\nAll must pass.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":122,"cache_read_input_tokens":20535,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":122},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd6a4346-a79d-4fbc-9791-90b9d0ba34fd","uuid":"ececec02-4ac5-4bea-8bed-3bdfd99e48b6"}
